"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-3ID","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":14295,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/19\/sunnah-umar-or-prophet\/","url_meta":{"origin":14299,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Sunnah: Are you commanded to follow Umar or the Prophet?","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 19, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Salim reported: A man from Syria asked Abdullah ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, about continuing after Umrah to Hajj. Ibn Umar said, \u201cIt is lawful.\u201d The man said, \u201cBut your father prohibited it.\u201d Ibn Umar said, \u201cIs the command to follow my father or the Messenger of\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":12146,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/02\/12\/touch-al-hajar-al-aswad\/","url_meta":{"origin":14299,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Hajj: Touch black stone, but it has no powers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 12, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"'Abis ibn Rabi'ah reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, came to the black stone and he kissed it. Umar said, \u201cVerily, I know you are only a stone with no power to harm or benefit me. Were it not that I saw the Prophet, peace and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33739,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/10\/20\/sahaba-criticized-united\/","url_meta":{"origin":14299,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ikhtilaf: Companions criticized leadership but remained united","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 20, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdur Rahman ibn Yazid reported: Uthman, may Allah be pleased with him, prayed four cycles at Mina. Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud said, \u201cI prayed it as two cycles with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, as well as Abu Bakr and Umar.\u201d Mu\u2019awiyah ibn Qurrah added: Abdullah then prayed\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15670,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/08\/14\/fasting-or-not-arafah\/","url_meta":{"origin":14299,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Hajj: Fasting or not on the day of Arafat","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 14, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: I have performed the Hajj pilgrimage with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and he did not fast during Arafat. I performed it with Abu Bakr and he did not fast, with Umar and he did not fast, and with Uthman and he did not\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":38371,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/10\/24\/hajj-purifies-sin\/","url_meta":{"origin":14299,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Hajj: Pilgrimage purifies from sins and poverty","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 24, 2022","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cPerform the Hajj and \u2018Umrah pilgrimages, one after another, for they both erase poverty and sins just as the furnace removes impurity from iron, gold, and silver. There is no reward for an accepted Hajj\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36410,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/30\/salat-like-hajj-umrah\/","url_meta":{"origin":14299,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Prayer rewarded like pilgrimage","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 30, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Umamah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever leaves his house with ritual purification for a prescribed prayer, his reward will be like one performing a Hajj pilgrimage in a state of sanctity. Whoever leaves to glorify Allah in the forenoon, laboring only\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/14299","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embe